They are often found in groups of five or more and they employ rudimentary combat tactics, often attacking recklessly with repeated swings and long combos that leave them open. At times, you may spot an Albinauric performing quick cartwheels on the battlefield, displaying agility despite their stature.

description: The Chanting Winged Dames of Liurnia of The Lakes are equally hostile as they are suspicious.

extra_json: {"drops": ["42 Runes", "Rainbow Stone", "Rickety Shield", "Falchion", "String", "Glowstone", "", "Rainbow Stone"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a47d8c4l0i6z1hixh46ze7d0j.png", "location": "Caves and beaches of Limgrave, such as Dissenter's Cave."}

extra_json: {"drops": ["Fire Monk Hood", "Fire Monk Armor", "Fire Monk Gauntlets", "Fire Monk Greaves", "Monk's Flamemace", "Smouldering Butterfly", "Fire Blossom"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a4a39c2l0i6z1owhunir5sz7ok.png", "location": "East Liurnia of The Lakes"}

description: Flame Guardians are slender humanoids dressed in simple white garbs and wearing a bronze mask, concealing their identity. They are equipped with long, flaming poles/staves and wield fire magic.

name: Gnoll
description: Hungry Gnolls are usually found eating from dead bodies which makes them vulnerable to surprise or stealth attacks, but they are quick and unforgivingly lethal. They come in different classes, some of the wield a sword and use it very acrobatically, other use shields and some even are able to cast thunder.

name: Godrick Soldier
description: The Godrick Soldiers of the Lands Between now roam the landscape, their clothes rags, hoping to rebuild their lives
extra_json: {"drops": ["64 - 77 Runes"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a3a9029l0i6z27h60v22c5sisi.png", "location": "Gatefront Ruins, Castle Morne, Stormgate, Roaming the Limgrave landscape"}

name: Golem
description: Golems lay inactive in the hills of Stormhill, but those foolish enough to wake them will soon curse their fate
extra_json: {"drops": ["3x Smithing Stone Shard", "844~1039 Runes"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f69f23c47l0i6z297epd0jcox8d.png", "location": "West ruins of Stormhill., Castle Morne Entrance, Ainsel River Well, Leyndell, Royal Capital"}

name: Highwayman
description: Former foot soldiers who have turned to banditry. Clandestine and secluded from civilazation, now they lie in hidden caves.

name: Great Horned Tragoth
description: Invading another world. Defeat Great Horned Tragoth!
extra_json: {"drops": ["158 Runes", "Furlcalling Finger Remedy", "Rune Arc", "Bull-Goat Helm", "Bull-Goat Armor", "Bull-Goat Gauntlets", "Bull-Goat Greaves"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a1704cdl0i6z2ohrqnekxuveon.png", "location": "Ruin-Strewn Precipice"}

name: Gold Dragon Cult Knight
description: Exceedingly tough and skillful Knight, a golden armor-wearing menace lethal to most. Highly trained warrior and a threatening adversary due to its fine combat skills.
extra_json: {"drops": ["Dragon Cult Prayerbook", "", "Leyndell Knight Set", ""], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a37a5f1l0i6z2ptkcpanfvzxk.png", "location": "Liurnia of The Lakes"}

name: Imp
description: Imps infest many catacombs in the Lands Between, although some theorize they could be protecting their secrets

name: Imp Miner
description: Small and agile creatures that typically conceal themselves within a smokescreen., Often wielding an axe or a flail amd performing flying attacks.

name: Invisible Warrior
description: Sneak warriors, patient and quick to get in your back.

name: Juno Hoslow, Knight Of Blood
extra_json: {"drops": ["158 Runes", "Rune Arc", "Furlcalling Finger Remedy", "Hoslow's Petal Whip", "Hoslow's Helm", "Hoslow's Armor", "Hoslow's Gauntlets", "Hoslow's Greaves"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a6452b7l0i6z39vw4cv451i5eh.png", "location": "Mountaintops of the Giants"}

name: Imp
description: Imps infest many catacombs in the Lands Between, although some theorize they could be protecting their secrets

name: Lesser Burial Watchdog
description: A living construct fashioned after felines and hounds, made to watch over catacombs. These constructs wield massive stone weaponry and are attuned to different elements.

name: Knight Of Zamor
description: Knights of Zamor are slender humanoids with long hair, wielding a peculiar curved blade. These warriors are graceful and perform almost dance-like maneuvers as they weave across the battlefield. As denizens of the Mountaintops of the Giants, Knights of Zamor are strongly attuned to Frost, utilizing its powers to bolster their swordplay.

name: Lesser Pumpkin Head
description: The Lesser Pumpkin Head is a weaker variant of the Pumpkin Head. It appears to be an outcast due to its appearance and is mainly used as one of a weapon to fight against intruders and trespassers alike. The Lesser Pumpkin Head can be seen wearing a Pumpkin Helm, a distressed cloak, and wields a large club.
extra_json: {"drops": ["Pumpkin Helm", "Sanctuary Stone", "273~293 Runes"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a590e96l0i6z3ozc8rcbywnwpk.png", "location": "Castle Morne, Raya Lucaria Academy, Limgrave"}

name: Lesser Ulcerated Tree Spirit
description: A guardian that sleeps deep within the crypt of Stormveil Castle. It is quick and very aggressive when it attacks and moves similar to a centipede with its multiple legs. The Lesser Ulcerated Tree Spirit also features two large arms and a tail that it mainly uses to swing around or to slam the ground.

name: Living Jar
description: The Living Jar, a walking vase that has long arms used for reaching and attacking their foes. A Living Jar may appear small in a group and it can also appear as a singular giant entity, capable of using slow, yet strong attacks.

name: Lesser Wormface
description: Lesser Wormface may not be as large as Wormface itself but they can be found roaming around in groups around Crumbling Farum Azula.

name: Maneuverable Flamethrower
description: Large wagons operated from the inside that shoot fire from a sculpture's mouth.

name: Marionette Gargoyle
description: The Marionette Gargoyle are statues within Raya Lucaria Academy that have been reanimated with magical properties. They mainly fly in the air and wield a scythe that they use to attack their foes. They are usually found on posts, pretending to be statues.

name: Marionette Soldier
description: Marionette Soldiers are puppets that are created and given life by superior being that reside within Raya Lucaria Academy. Their purpose is to protect and stop intruders from entering the institute. These soldiers appear to have multiple arms wielding more than one weapon, making them unpredictable in regards to how they will strike.
extra_json: {"drops": ["Marionette Soldier Helm"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a0988d8l0i6z4hc87seey9tml6.png", "location": "Raya Lucaria Academy, Academy Gate Town, Raya Lucaria Crystal Tunnel, Witchbane Ruins"}

name: Miner
description: The ever working miners of Limgrave know no life but their toil, and will fiercely defend it
extra_json: {"drops": ["92 Runes", "Explosive Stone", "Smithing Stone [1]"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a01fd7dl0i6z4m61s5fhcnqbsl.png", "location": "Limgrave Tunnels, Sellia Crystal Tunnel, Ruin-Strewn Precipice"}

name: Mounted Northern Mercenary
description: Mounted Northern Mercenaries are often seen guarding important deliveries and outposts, such as Stormgate

name: Mounted Knight
extra_json: {"drops": ["Ash of War: Golden Vow"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f69e8a2b8l0i6z4x8r2r0q9rh0e.png", "location": "North-east region of Limgrave, North of Liurnia of the Lakes"}

name: Noble Sorcerer
description: Noble Sorcerers are frail old men wearing tattered garbs and a dirty yellow cape. They use a standard glintstone staff as both a sorcery catalyst and walking stick.

name: Misbegotten
description: The Misbegotten are small humanoid creatures with small wings on their backs and a tail that reaches to the ground. Treated as slaves or worse from the time they are born, they rush in attack wildly and ruthlessly with their Iron Cleavers.
extra_json: {"drops": ["Iron Cleaver", "Old Fang", "59 Runes"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f69f69a20l0i6z54ww74ju60bty.png", "location": "Castle Morne, Weeping Peninsula, Mt. Gelmir"}

name: Kaiden Sellsword
description: Kaiden Sellswords roam the land, looking to be hired for several protection roles
extra_json: {"drops": ["282 Runes ", "Dismounter", "", "Frozen Raisin", "Kaiden Helm", "Kaiden Armor", "Kaiden Gauntlets", "Kaiden Trousers"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f69d7e1b7l0i6z5a4ncivwwpp2qj.png", "location": "Throughout Limgrave and Stormhill"}

name: Omen
description: A large ogre that is kept imprisoned within the grounds of Stormveil Castle. It appears to be battered and treated violently to discipline it, and used as a weapon to fight against trespassers.

name: Pendulum Statue
description: A golden statue that sits on a small wagon. Attached to it are two pendulum blades that can extend to capture its prey. The Pendulum Statue is being controlled by an unkown creature that rests within it, only by opening its chest will it reveal its root-like tentacles.

name: Old Knight Istvan
description: Invading another world. Defeat Old Knight Istvan!
extra_json: {"drops": ["84 Runes", "Rune Arc", "Furlcalling Finger Remedy", "Scaled Helm", "Scaled Armor", "Scaled Gauntlets", "Scaled Greaves"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a1f8766l0i6z5q9r5tu6mrj36h.png", "location": "Stormhill"}

name: Pumpkin Head
description: The breaking disrupted the flora and fauna of the region. Some took a rather intense liking to the larger plants that emerged
extra_json: {"drops": ["291 Runes", "Pumpkin Helm", "Sanctuary Stone"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a3a46ccl0i6z5xed8ncsfqghvd.png", "location": "Castle Morne, Weeping Peninsula"}

name: Raya Lucaria Sorcerer
description: Academicians of the Raya Lucaria Academy. These sholars dedicate their lives to learning and mastering the art of sorcery and serve one superiror sorcerer who resides within the institute. They are able to use glintstone sorcery to strike their foes from afar, and are still capable of using their weapon for close-quarters combat.
extra_json: {"drops": ["Academy Glintstone Staff", "Raya Lucarian Robe", "Sorcerer Manchettes", "Sorcerer Leggings"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f69cf2d89l0i6z60v1napt1t9k63.png", "location": "Raya Lucaria Academy"}

name: Rileigh The Idle
description: Invading another world. Defeat Rileigh the Idle!
extra_json: {"drops": ["84 Runes", "Rune Arc", "Furlcalling Finger Remedy", "Crepus's Vial", "Black-Key Bolt x20"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a59863fl0i6z6burs88c0miyu.png", "location": "Altus Plateau"}

name: Revenant
description: A grotesque amalgamation of limbs, the Revenant is a creature with the body structure of an arachnid and the face of a human. Much like a spider, it possesses many limbs that seem to have been grafted onto its body, taken from diseased humans. The Revenant is capable of traveling through portals it creates with a peculiar form of magic, swiftly emerging behind a foe to catch them off guard.
extra_json: {"drops": ["4,103 Runes", "Ghost Glovewort (2)", "Rowa Fruit"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f69f71f60l0i6z6caa01v3eaefsv.png", "location": "Liurnia of the Lakes"}

name: Servant Of Rot
description: Servants of Rot relish in the pungent miasma expelled by Poison Flowers. Their bodies are heavily mutated by the rot, their heads transformed into large crowns of fungi. These presumably former humans know only the rot and they worship it like a deity, bathed in its fog of decay.

name: Raya Lucarian Warden
description: Wardens roam the halls of the Raya Lucaria Academy, armed and watchful for furtive marauders.

name: Soldier
description: Soldiers defend the many outposts of the Lords from incoming threats, such as the Tarnished
extra_json: {"drops": ["33~64 Runes", "Lordsworn's Straight Sword", "Dagger"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f69d1e7e0l0i6z6mt86j6rq8kd7k.png", "location": "Stormveil Castle, Stormhill, Main Limgrave, Weeping Peninsula"}

name: Skeleton Mage
description: Skeleton Mages are usually found on graveyards in Liurnia of the Lakes. They can out from the ground, they can be found in groups, wielding scythes and constantly casting a spell launching ghostly skulls against you.

name: Skeleton
description: Skeletons rise from cemeteries and ruins of the Lands Between, attacking relentlessly any who approach
extra_json: {"drops": ["35 Runes"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a529d76l0i6z7317q6dcu048df.png", "location": "In the beaches and dungeons of Limgrave, and in the cemetery area of Stormhill"}

name: Slender Wayfarer
description: A rare and long-haired creature, tall and slender, often found at the shore.

name: Swordstress
description: Nimble warriors protecting and patrolling the eternal cities.

name: Troll
description: The Trolls of the Lands Between are frequently enslaved for defensive positions, but are also used in lieu of beasts of burden
extra_json: {"drops": ["≈1000 Runes", "Smithing Stone Shard"], "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/creatures/17f6a2e0377l0i6z7guw0djley785.png", "location": "Along the road north of the Collapsed bridge"}

name: Troll Knight
description: Trolls are often employed to guard key locations, such as staircases large enough to accommodate their massive bodies. Often unmatched in strength, it bears the question... What manner of creature poses enough of a threat such that the mighty troll would find itself in need of heavy armor...?

name: Undead Soldier
description: Undead creatures, decayed and struggling to maintain balance while roaming the fields of The Lands Between.

name: Twinsage Sorcerer
description: Twinsage Sorcerers are distinguished from other scholars by the crowns worn on their head, depicting the Twinsage Conspectus, with distinct blue crystals forming at the top of the twin heads.

name: Wraith Caller
description: As their name suggests, Wraith Callers are equipped with Wraith Calling Bells that they use to channel death magic, summoning vengeful spirits to attack those that dare intrude upon the ruins of Liurnia. Devout worshippers of the Revenants, Wraith Callers are able to utilize the Revenants' dimensional portals, albeit to a lesser extent.

name: Bridge Of Sacrifice
description: A busy bridge swarming with iron-clad foes. Be prepared to engage in an array of melee, ranged and artillery attacks or attempt to push past them

name: Church Of Elleh
description: Church of Elleh is a ruined building that hides a Site of Grace. The rooftop has caved in and offers no protection from the elements, and weeds are overtaking the walls, but this doesn't stop merchants from seeking what little shelter is on offer

name: Deathtouched Catacombs
description: Catacombs filled with the stench of death, Skeletons dwell in the shadows

name: Church Of Dragon Communion
description: The dilapidated remains of the Church of Dragon Communion showcase the ruin that came to the land. But could a flame still linger at its altar??

name: Coastal Cave
description: Coastal Cave is a dark opening on the side of a cliff. Its mossy depths are overrun by hostile humanoid creatures, but those who brave it may find passage to new lands

name: Dragon-burnt Ruins
description: Dragon-Burnt Ruins are what remains of the housing area among Agheel Lake, long lost to the deadly attacks of the fierce Agheel Dragon

name: Forlorn Hound Evergaol
description: The southern Evergaol of Limgrave, before the entrance to Weeping Peninsula

name: Fringefolk Hero's Grave
description: Fingefolk Hero's Grave is a dark and secluded location within the Cave of Knowledge. The confused and aimless dwell within

name: Fort Haight
description: The overrun fort of Kenneth Haith, the alleged next ruler of Limgrave

name: Divine Tower Of Limgrave
description: Closed with a giant set of doors. It looks like you need some pieces to interact with the tower.

name: Gatefront Ruins
description: Gatefront Ruins is what remains of the now destroyed barracks near the fortification. Despite its poor state, it is a heavily guarded location by those loyal to Stormveil

name: Limgrave Tunnels
description: Limgrave Tunnels are a mine harvested for Glimstone. Its zealous miners don't dare venture into its hidden chambers, for fear of the hoarder Troll within

name: Groveside Cave
description: Groveside Cave is a small refuge for wildlife in Limgrave. Its proximity to water and ease of access make it a sought-after shelter against bad weather, but those who venture in don't seem to return

name: Minor Erdtree (mistwood)
description: Easily distiguished from the rest of the trees in Mistwood Forest.

name: Highroad Cave
description: A cave that houses a tomb, deep within. It is situated at the northmost part of Limgrave. It has been inhabited by a pack of Wolves, Land Octopuses, and Giant Bats

name: Mistwood
description: Mistwood is a Location in Elden Ring. The Mistwood region is located in the Eastern part of Limgrave. Tiered terrain, small beaches, and luscious forests occupied by Lesser Runebears are the defining features of this region.

name: Mistwood Ruins
description: Concealed by the thriving growth of vegetation, these ruins are kept out of sight by the veil of nature itself. But there's more to it than what you see

name: Murkwater Catacombs
description: An underground cemetery that is located at the north-east side of Agheel Lake in Limgrave. Once a place for peaceful rest for fallen heroes, it is now infested by goblins.

name: Murkwater Cave
description: A dark cave halfway through the Murkwater River

name: Siofra River Well
description: A mystical underground region filled with its own set of skies and stars. Beware, it is teeming with creatures big and small alike

name: Smoldering Church
description: The Last Church in Limgrave before reaching Caelid

name: Stormgate
description: The Stormgate is a heavily guarded area that marks the border within Limgrave and Stormhill. Only the foolhardy would rush such against such odds

name: Stormfoot Catacombs
description: Stormfoot Catacombs were meant as a restful place for the deceased, but its now overrun by Goblins. Its deepest secrets are secured by the Guardian of the Burial Tree

name: Stormhill
description: Stormhill is a Location in Elden Ring. Stormhill is the upper half area of Limgrave, between its central river and Stormveil.

name: Stormhill Evergaol
description: The Brave and Foolish alike dare venture into the Stormhill Evergaol and face its relentless knight in battle

name: Stormhill Shack
description: The Stormhill Shack is a dilapidated shelter formerly used to house hunters in the area. A Site of Grace offers a needed moment of rest for those traveling nearby

name: Stranded Graveyard
description: Stranded Graveyard is a dark and secluded location within the Cave of Knowledge. The confused and aimless dwell within

name: Summonwater Village
description: D, Hunter of The Dead, warns you of this nearby village taken over by death, known as Summonwater Village

name: Third Church Of Marika
description: The Ruins of an Old Church found in the Mistwood. The most prominent sight here is a statue of a lady with her arms outstretched

name: Warmaster's Shack
description: Small shack in a remote area near north-central Stormhill.

name: Waypoint Ruins
description: Waypoint Ruins consists of a group of broken buildings and abandoned campsites, now overrun with poisonous flowers and their crazed caretaker

name: Ailing Village
description: A small, abandoned village nestled within a forested area north of the Castle Morne Rampart. This village is host to long-dilapidated dwellings, inhabited only by hostile Demi-humans.

name: Bridge Of Sacrifice
description: A busy bridge swarming with iron-clad foes. Be prepared to engage in an array of melee, ranged and artillery attacks or attempt to push past them

name: Callu Baptismal Church
description: A dilapidated church, presumably frequented by the former residents of Ailing Village. Now it lies in ruin, its congregation replaced by a family of mutant vermin feasting on the remains of  unfortunate travelers

name: Church Of Pilgrimage
description: The Church of Pilgrimage is a broken building situated at the top of the cliff in the north of the Weeping Peninsula. Even with the walls and roof destroyed pilgrims still make the journey to visit this church

name: Castle Morne
description: Remants of a chaos swept castle, teeming with iron-clad enemies -now engulfed with fire, piles of remains and ruin.

name: Demi-human Forest Ruins
description: Demi-Humans congregate here to worship their queen. Defeating her will reward players with the Demi-Human Queen's Staff, which is excellent for beginner mages.

name: Earthbore Cave
description: Earthbore Cave is a small dark cave on the side of the Cliffside between Limgrave and Weeping Peninsula. One might be able to hear the squeaks of rats and the snoring of a large beast deep within if you listen closely

name: Forest Lookout Tower
description: A run-down tower built on the edge of the cliffs of the Weeping Peninsula, located west of the Bridge of Sacrifice.

name: Impaler's Catacombs
description: The Impaler's Catacombs are found in the east side of the Weeping Peninsula. Once used to store the bodies of the dead, it is now crawling with Imps.

name: Fourth Church Of Marika
description: The ruins of a lonely church, sitting atop a plateau west of the peninsula. Despite its current state, the altar remains intact and ghostly knights still roam the fields nearby, perhaps restless and duty-bound to safeguarding the area...

name: Minor Erdtree (weeping Peninsula)
description: One of the large Erdtree's found in the Weeping Peninsula. An Erdtree Avatar charges at those who approach

name: Isolated Merchant's Shack
description: Found at the western edge of the Weeping Peninsula, this lonesome hut is home to but a single person who has long adapted to a life of seclusion

name: Oridys's Rise
description: A lone observation tower atop a plateau in the east of the Weeping Peninsula. Long since abandoned, the entrance is barred by a seal, presenting travelers with a small challenge

name: Morne Tunnel
description: A dark and hidden tunnel that is inhabited by Misbegottens and Miners.

name: Tombsward Cave
description: Hidden cave in the forest teeming with poison-filled creatures.

name: Tombsward Ruins
description: The ruins of a former burial ground. Next to nothing remains here, yet squires still roam the dark tunnels beneath. Perhaps protecting the graves of their former noble masters..

name: Tombsward Catacombs
description: The Tombsward Catacombs are hidden inside the mountain near the Minor Erdtree in the Weeping Peninsula. Once filled with the bodies of the dead, armed skeletons now rise to chase away those that wish to explore its depths.

name: Tower Of Return
description: A dilapidated tower guarded by foot soldiers and mounted cavalry. Makeshift wooden platforms and ladders line the inside of the tower, allowing it to retain some function as a lookout point and a mount for ballistae

name: Weeping Evergaol
description: An evergaol located on the western landmass of the Weeping Peninsula. A formidable opponent is imprisoned within

name: Witchbane Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in western Weeping Peninsula. Overgrown with thick shrubs and poisonous flowers, this decrepit landmark invites only misery and dread.

name: Academy Crystal Cave
description: The depths of the Raya Lucaria Academy are rich in rose-tinted crystals, imbued with the natural magic of the area

name: Academy Gate Town
description: The sunken remains of the academy town

name: Ainsel River Well
description: A small structure housing a lift that takes you down to the Ainsel River.

name: Artist's Shack
description: A small cabin at North Liurnia of The Lakes. Its strongly perceived tranquility seems overshadowed by oblivion.

name: Bellum Church
description: Located past the ruins and the forested area guarded by Mounted Knights.

name: Bellum Highway
description: Outside the East Raya Lucaria Gate

name: Black Knife Catacombs
description: Black Knife Catacombs homes many skeletons and crabs within its depths, find and defeat the Black Knife Assassin within to obtain their dagger.

name: Caria Manor
description: A large estate situated far to the north of Liurnia.

name: Boilprawn Shack
description: Small cozy shack where Blackguard Big Boggart resides.

name: Carian Study Hall
description: A large library-like location full of spectres

name: Chapel Of Anticipation
description: A small starting building with trail leading to an area occupied by a gnarly Grafted Scion

name: Chelona's Rise
description: A tower overlooking the southern-most tip of Liurnia of the lakes

name: Church Of Inhibition
description: The remnants of an old church in the north of Liurnia, just before the Altus Plateau.

name: Cathedral Of Manus Celes
description: A large church atop the southern plateau of Liurnia.

name: Church Of Irith
extra_json: {"Liurnia of the Lakes": "A peaceful church at the back of Stormveil Castle.", "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/locations/17f69eb0b5al0i2mfvs8tpdxql60r.png", "region": "Limgrave"}

name: Church Of Vows
description: It is here, at the Church of Vows, that the great houses of the Erdtree and the Moon were joined by the matrimonial bond between red-haired Radagon and Rennala of the Full Moon. That is why it holds in view the monuments of both houses, the Erdtree of the Capital and the Academy of Raya Lucaria.

name: Converted Fringe Tower
description: A tower found on the fringe in the northeastern tip of Liurnia.

name: Converted Tower
description: An abandoned tower

name: Cuckoo's Evergaol
description: Evergaol located on the western landmass of Liurnia. A powerful force stirs within.

name: Deep Ainsel Well
description: A deep well leading to the Moonlight Altar from the underground Grand Cloister.

name: Divine Tower Of Liurnia
description: Divine Tower of Liurnia is a Location in Elden Ring. The Divine Tower of Liurnia is found in Liurnia of the Lakes and is reached by taking the lift down at the secret area of Carian Study Hall.

name: Frenzied Flame Village
description: A village in Liurnia gripped in the madness of Three Fingers. Its denizens know nothing but the fiery frenzy burning within them

name: Grand Lift Of Dectus
description: A massive lift platform found between Liurnia and the Altus Plateau. The mechanism that operates the lift is barred by four Guardian Statues, requiring the brandishing of a special artifact for them to release their hold

name: Highway Lookout Tower
description: A lone tower overlooking the Liurnia main road on the eastern landmass

name: Jarburg
description: Jarburg was a peaceful village, but the effects of the Shattering affected even the otherwise amicable Living Jar

name: Kingsrealm Ruins
description: A ruined area, only seemingly bare.

name: Lakeside Crystal Cave
description: Hidden on the southwestern cliffs of Liurnia of the Lakes, a winding cave carved by large crystals

name: Laskyar Ruins
description: Ruins of a sunken structure beset by fog, found amidst the marshes of south Liurnia.

name: Lunar Estate Ruins
description: The ruins of a large estate found atop the southwestern plateau of Liurnia.

name: Malefactor's Evergaol
description: An evergaol overlooking the vast lakes. An ever burning flame resides within

name: Minor Erdtree (liurnia Southwest)
extra_json: {"Liurnia of the Lakes": "This ancient Erdtree overlooks the lakes from the southwest", "image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/locations/17f69f56f55l0i2mhypmucze7mfrzc.png", "region": "Limgrave"}

name: Moonfolk Ruins
description: Ruins found in the southwest of the Liurnia of the Lakes region

name: Purified Ruins
description: The holy remains now lie in ruin

name: Ranni's Rise
description: A tower beset by large chunks of glintstone emerging from the ground and penetrating its interiors. Home to a mysterious figure observing The Lands Between

name: Raya Lucaria Crystal Tunnel
description: One of the vast networks of tunnels used prominently for the academy's crystal mining operation.

name: Renna's Rise
description: A Tower of the Three Sisters, belonging to Renna. It houses Ranni's Snow Witch Armor Set

name: Revenger's Shack
description: An isolated shack north of the Minor Erdtree. Bodies litter the ground inside the shack, possibly belonging to those one has taken revenge upon

name: Ringleader's Evergaol
description: An evergaol where a nortorious assassin is incarcerated

name: Road's End Catacombs
description: Catacombs at the end of the world..

name: Rose Church
description: The ruins of a former church aptly named Rose Church, for its walls are now festering with scarlet rot and overgrown with bloodroses.

name: Royal Grave Evergaol
description: An evergaol constructed for the Carian Royal family in the plains east of the royal estate

name: Ruin-strewn Precipice
description: A steep precipice with abundant caves in the insides all the way through

name: Seluvis's Rise
description: A tower bequeathed unto Preceptor Seluvis. Serves as his personal study as he delves into the sorcerous arts.

name: Slumbering Wolf's Shack
description: A small shack nestled at the side of a cliff, only accessible through a long winding cave system.   A woman and her wolf companion rest here.

name: Stillwater Cave
description: A dark and murky cave beset by a poisonous miasma. Home to servants of rot, relishing in the presence of the giant poisonblooms endemic to the cave

name: Temple Quarter
description: Ruined by the breaking, the Temple Quarter is now overrun with dangerous creatures, ready to attack any who come near

name: Testu's Rise
description: An observation tower found in the middle of a lone isle in Liurnia. The entrance is sealed by impish magic and presents a challenge to would-be visitors

name: The Four Belfries
description: As its name suggests, The Four Belfries is a hill with four large bell towers overlooking Liurnia from the west. Each belfry hosts a waygate that transports travelers to various locations

name: Village Of The Albinaurics
description: The cursemongers have destroyed the Village of the Albinaurics, but perhaps their hope to reach the promised city is not yet lost

name: Abandoned Cave
description: Long time abandoned cave.

name: Caelem Ruins
description: A set of perpetually burning ruins in western Caelid. The Caelid Highway cuts through these ruins which are heavily guarded by mobile flamethrowers and swarming with burning reanimated corpses

name: Caelid Catacombs
description: A labyrinth of Scarlet Rot-soaked floors and tunnels.

name: Caelid Waypoint Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in southwest Caelid, along the highway. Long abandoned, the ruins have become home to all manner of creatures that revel in the decay and putrefaction brought on by the scarlet rot

name: Aeonia Swamp
description: The Swamp of Aeonia is nestled in the center of the Caelid region. What were once flourishing plains filled with rich flora and fauna are now reduced to a cesspool of death and decay. A high concentration of the dreaded scarlet rot has mutated the very earth itself, twisting the creatures and plant life that once called this home.

name: Cathedral Of Dragon Communion (caelid)
description: The Cathedral of Dragon Communion has long been destroyed, but those who seek to commune with draconic power may yet access its power

name: Church Of The Plague
description: A dilapidated church found in the cliffs east of Sellia, Town of Sorcery

name: Fort Gael
description: A ruined fort in a ruined land,

name: Gael Tunnel
description: A set of tunnels found on the western edge of Caelid, along the border to Limgrave

name: Forsaken Ruins
description: The Forsaken Ruins consists of a group of broken buildings and abandoned campsites. It is located in Caelid and is gaurded by a Giant Crow

name: Gaol Cave
description: Found at the west of Caelid.

name: Gowry's Shack
description: A lone shack found below the eastern hills near Sellia, Town of Sorcery.

name: Minor Erdtree Catacombs
description: Minor Erdtree Catacombs is a Location in Elden Ring. The Minor Erdtree Catacombs is found in Caelid, beneath the Minor Erdtree. Players can reach this location by traveling east from where the region meets with Limgrave and then looking for the entrance behind the tree, in the north.

name: Redmane Castle
description: A small castle that is heavily guarded at the castle's outskirts by Radahn Knights and Soldiers. The Redmane Castle serves as the gathering point for warriors alike who are wanting to participate in the Radahn Festival

name: Minor Erdtree (caelid)
description: The Minor Erdtree of Caelid, found in the northwest near the border to Limgrave.

name: Sellia Crystal Tunnel
description: The crystal mining operation of Sellia is overseen by greedy and aggressive insectoids

name: Sellia Evergaol
description: Outside of Sellia Evergaol

name: Sellia Gateway
description: The gateway leading to Sellia, Town of Socrcery

name: Sellia, Town Of Sorcery
description: A once-great town renowned for its study of the sorcerous arts. Now lying in ruin, the ghosts of its former scholars still roam the streets.

name: Smoldering Church
description: The Last Church in Limgrave before reaching Caelid

name: Shack Of The Rotting
description: An old worn-down shack overlooking a long stretch of cliffs in western Caelid.

name: Street Of Sages Ruins
description: The sages of Caelid are no more, and their former district is now the dwelling of perfumers and their poisonous flowers

name: War-dead Catacombs
description: Catacombs for those who have died a glorious battle death

name: Capital Outskirts
description: Capital Outskirts is a Location in Elden Ring. The Capital Outskirts sub-region lies in the Eastern area of the Altus Plateau and is the region just outside Leyndell, Royal Capital but still within the capital's outer walls. Beware of Skeletons rising from their graves and rocks flying out of the capital toward the battlegrounds when exploring the area.

name: Altus Tunnel
description: The Altus tunnels were once used to supply the lands with quality crystals

name: Dominula, Windmill Village
description: Dominula, Windmill Village is a Location in Elden Ring. The Dominula, Windmill Village  is found in Altus Plateau. East of the "Road of iniquity Side Path"sight of grace. Follow the main path southeast then bend east.

name: East Windmill Pasture
description: East Pasture Outskirsts of Windmill Village. True to its name, it can be identified by the still-working windmill placed in the center of the pasture.

name: Golden Lineage Evergaol
description: An evergaol located on within the Altus Plateau.

name: Hermit Merchant's Shack
description: Nestled on a cliff within the confines of the Royal Capital, this shack is home to a humble merchant, who has chosen a life of seclusion

name: Altus Tunnel
description: The Altus tunnels were once used to supply the lands with quality crystals

name: Leyndell, Royal Capital
description: Leyndell, Royal Capital is a Location in Elden Ring. The Leyndell, Royal Capital region is only accessible to players who have gathered two Great Runes or by following Ranni the Witch quest line and defeating Fia's Champions near the Great Waterfall Crest Site of Grace in the Deeproot Depths, and has content for highly leveled gameplay. For a detailed walkthrough, please visit the walkthrough page for Leyndell, Royal Capital Legacy Dungeon here.

name: Lux Ruins
description: Long forgotten ruins among golden trees, swarmed with demi-humans protecting the undergound chamber.

name: Old Altus Tunnel
description: An old mining site, still active to this day. Its tunnels echo with the grunts and groans of the commoners, tirelessly slaving away, grinding at the rich reservoir of crystals deep within

name: Minor Erdtree Church
description: What's left of the Church of the Minor Erdtree

name: Sealed Tunnel
description: Not as small or abandoned as it looks.

name: Stormcaller Church
description: A lonely church on a steppe

name: The Shaded Castle
description: An abandoned and Decrepit castle found in the northern region between the Mt. Gelmir and the Altus Plateau regions. The castle is half sunken into a poisonous bog, with the air tinged yellow by the fumes.

name: Woodfolk Ruins
description: Woodfolk Ruins, guarded by Limgrave's creatures, can be found near the Minor Erdtree within Altus Plateau.

name: Corpse-stench Shack
description: A run-down shack amidst burning corpses past the site of a recent battle.

name: Writheblood Ruins
description: Writheblood ruins, with nearest minor erdtree in background

name: Craftsman's Shack
description: A series of long-abandoned huts found directly south of the volcano

name: Gelmir Hero's Grave
description: Large Catacombs housing an ancient hero of Mt. Gelmir.

name: Hermit's Shack
description: An abandoned shack along the western edge of Mt. Gelmir

name: Fort Laiedd
description: Fort Laiedd is found on the western edge of Mt. Gelmir. A fort left broken, still occupied by those who won the battle

name: Perfumer's Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in Altus Plateau, far to the west and below Mt. Gelmir.

name: Hermit Village
description: A dilapidated village southeast of Mt. Gelmir. Now home to Demi-Humans.

name: Sage's Cave
description: Sage's Cave is a dark opening in the side of a mountain. Its dark depths are overrun by hostile undead, but those who brave it may find treasures beyond compare

name: Second Church Of Marika
description: Second of the four Churches of Marika where players can gather a Sacred Tear for their flask.

name: Unsightly Catacombs
description: A burial grounds crawling with Misbegotten creatures found deep beneath the Perfumer's Ruins. Despite its decrepit state, the catacombs give off a trace of fragrant aromas juxtaposed by the scent of the ancient dead

name: Seethewater Cave
description: A cave found along the Seethewater Ravine.

name: Wyndham Catacombs
description: Burial grounds located beneath Wyndham Ruins.

name: Volcano Cave
description: A cave system at the highest point of Mt. Gelmir, made into a home by a family of Demi-Humans hiding their maddened Queen.

name: Wyndham Ruins
description: A large set of ruins atop a burial grounds. The reanimated dead still roam the area

name: Bestial Sanctum
description: The Beastial Sanctum is a refuge for those who feed on the dead. Beastly and deformed, the clergyman here will teach the ways of the beast to those who feed it

name: Dragonbarrow Cave
description: A small dungeon found beneath the Minor Erdtree in Dragonbarrow

name: Divine Tower Of Caelid
description: A massive tower found in central Dragonbarrow, north of Caelid. The sides of the tower are crumbling from the massive overgrowth protruding from the plateau

name: Deep Siofra Well
description: A second lift to the Siofra River.

name: Fort Faroth
description: Fort Faroth used to house the guardians of Caelid, but its defenders have long fallen, now bound to earth as hostile spirits

name: Lenne's Rise
description: An observation tower in the northeast of Dragonbarrow, off the path to the Bestial Sanctum

name: Isolated Merchant's Shack (dragonbarrow)
description: A lonesome hut found atop a plateau in western Dragonbarrow. Home to a hermit looking to part with various odds and ends... for a price

name: Castle Sol
description: A castle found in the northeast of the Mountaintops of the Giants. Stronghold of Commander Niall and his spectral knights

name: Church Of Repose
description: A small crumbled church high on the mountains

name: Forge Of The Giants
description: The giant's forge could contain a volcano.

name: Grand Lift Of Rold
description: The impressive Lift of Rold transports those who wield the right key. But could there be more than one destination??

name: Guardians' Garrison
description: Guardian's Garrison is staffed by Fire Priests, who zealously watch the road leading to the Giant's Forge

name: Giant-conquering Hero's Grave
description: A complex dungeon filled with invulnerable enemies and strange golden floor seals.

name: Shack Of The Lofty
description: A lone shack found in the Mountaintops of the Giants. This shack was once visited by a traveling maiden, but she had long since perished under the elements

name: Spiritcaller's Cave
description: A cave found by the Freezing Lake, heavily battered by the elements

name: Stargazer's Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in central Mountaintops of the Giants. The plateau it is sitting on is located between two bridges.

name: Zamor Ruins
description: The ancient Town of Zamor, now fallen to ruin. Its anzient order of knights still roam the snow-capped streets

name: Consecrated Snowfield Catacombs
description: The Catacombs of the fields leading to Miquella's Haligtree hide powerful secrets, but are zealously guarded

name: Apostate Derelict
description: A ruined church lying in the frozen north-west of the Consecrated Grounds

name: Heretical Rise
description: The secrets of Heretical Rise are closely guarded by hidden magic, but the tower is overrun with hostile Avionette Soldiers

name: Hidden Path To The Haligtree
description: The secret passage leading to Miquella's Haligtree has been polluted by Those Who Live in Dead

name: Yelough Anix Ruins
description: A set of ruins found in the northwest of the Consecrated Snowfield

name: Ordina, Liturgical Town
description: Ghost town inhabitated in the evergaol

name: Yelough Anix Tunnel
description: An icy tunnel on the southern edge of the Yelough Anix Ruins

name: Blue Cipher Ring
description: Item for online play. Puts the wearer in ready state to answer should someone in another world call for rescue. You will be summoned to their world as a hunter. When summoned to rescue another player, your objective will be to defeat the invader.

name: White Cipher Ring
description: Item for online play. Allows you to automatically request for a hunter from another world to come to your rescue when your world is invaded. (You may be unable to summon rescuers under certain circumstances). A lost mystic code, enchanted to take the form of a ring. One of the fetishes said to have been bestowed by the Two Fingers.

name: Furlcalling Finger Remedy
description: Item for online play. Craftable item. Reveals cooperative and competitive multiplayer signs. Co-op summoning signs will be shown in gold, while hostile summoning signs will be shown in red. Multiplayer begins when you summon a player from another world through their sign.

name: Tarnished's Furled Finger
description: Item for online play. Creates a summon sign for cooperative multiplayer. Your objective will be to defeat the area boss of the world to which you were summoned. A finger of corpse wax, furled like a hook. It is a relic of those who came before, left to help those who would come after.

name: Finger Severer
description: Item for online play.

name: Duelist's Furled Finger
description: Item for online play. Creates a summon sign for competitive multiplayer. Your objective will be to defeat the Host of Fingers of the world to which you were summoned. A finger of corpse wax, furled like a hook. The bronze adornments are the mark of a duelist.

name: Memory Of Grace
description: A phantom vision of the first grace, which once guided the Tarnished to the Lands Between. Lose all runes and return to last site of grace at which you rested. It all repeats. Be seen by the Elden Ring. Become the Elden Lord.

name: Tarnished's Wizened Finger
description: Item for online play. (Can also be used from the Messages menu.) Use to write messages. Your messages will be conveyed to other worlds, allowing other players to read them. A finger of corpse wax, so emaciated the bone is visible. It is a relic of those who came before, left to help those who would come after.

name: Taunter's Tongue
description: Item for online play. Lures in invaders. This allows your world to be invaded without any Furled Finger cooperators present, and it also shortens the interval between windows of opportunity for invasion. Additionally, enables the arrival of a second invader. (When two invaders are present, you will be limited to one cooperator.)

name: Bloody Finger
description: Item for online play. Attempts an invasion of another player's world. If successful, your objective will be to defeat the Host of Fingers of the world to which you were summoned. The nail of this finger is shot through with streaks of fresh, glistening blood. The finger's sickly pale skin feels nothing now, but the nail still aches with sweetest pain.

name: Small Golden Effigy
description: Online multiplayer item. Sends a summon sign for cooperative multiplayer to a nearby summoning pool. In cooperative multiplayer, you will be summoned to another world to help defeat the area boss.

name: Small Red Effigy
description: Item for online play. Sends a competitive sign to a nearby summoning pool. In competitive multiplayer, your objective will be to defeat the Host of Fingers of the world to which you were summoned.

name: Festering Bloody Finger
description: Item for online play.

name: Smithing Stone [3]
description: Stone used to smith a variety of armaments. A particularly hard specimen.

name: Smithing Stone [2]
description: Stone used to smith a variety of armaments. A large shard found in plenty. Strengthens armaments up to +6. Smithing stone is found throughout the Lands Between, and mining galleries built to excavate it can be found everywhere

name: Smithing Stone [4]
description: Stone used to smith a variety of armaments. A large and particularly hard specimen.

name: Smithing Stone [5]
description: Stone used to smith a variety of armamemnts. A rare specimen, it is tinged with gold.

name: Smithing Stone [7]
description: Stone used to smith a variey of armaments. Found in a polar region, it is semi-vitrified.

name: Smithing Stone [6]
description: Stone used to smith a variety of armaments. A larger rare specimen, it is tinged with gold.

name: Smithing Stone [8]
description: Stone used to smith a variety of armaments. Found in a polar region, it is semi-vitrified

name: Ancient Dragon Smithing Stone
description: Smithing stone made polishing a golden Gravel Stone. A scale of the Ancient Dragonlord, and hidden treasure of Farum Azula

name: Somber Smithing Stone [1]
description: Shard of smithing stone drained of color. Strengthens special armaments to +1. Special armements with unique characteristics cannot be strengthened with colored smithing stones. Number of steps and amount strengthened differ from standard equipment.

name: Somber Smithing Stone [2]
description: Large shard of smithing stone drained of color. Strengthens special armaments to +2. Special armements with unique characteristics cannot be strengthened with colored smithing stones. Number of steps and amount strengthened differ from standard equipment.

name: Recusant Finger
description: Item for online play.

name: Grave Glovewort [1]
description: White flower that blooms in catacombs. Each a soundless bell used to summon spirits. Strengthens ashes to +1. The art of strengthening ashes is known as spirit tuning. only a spirit tuner may perform this deed.

name: Grave Glovewort [2]
description: White flower that blooms in catacombs. Each a soundless bell used to summon spirits. Strengthens ashes to +2. Spirit tuning is not merely the simple act of imbuing strength. It is an art that lies somewhere between tuning an instrument and conducting a conversation, leaving both parties enriched.

name: Flask Of Crimson Tears
description: A sacred flask modelled after a golden holy chalice that was once graced by a tear of life. Filled with crimson tears, this flask restores HP with use. Rest at a site of grace to replenish. It is said that a Finger Maiden will bestow two such chalices upon the chosen Tarnished when they meet.

name: Flask Of Cerulean Tears
description: A sacred flask modelled after a golden holy chalice that was once graced by a tear of life. Filled with cerulean tears, this flask restores FP with use. Rest at a site of grace to replenish. It is said that a Finger Maiden will bestow two such chalices upon the chosen Tarnished when they meet.

name: Scriptstone
description: Ruin fragment inscribed with letters.  Craftable item. Reveals additional messages from other worlds. Words are gregarious things, drawn to one another much as people are.

name: Holy Water Pot

name: Glowstone

However, the effect is short-lived, and it lacks the diverse colors of rainbow stones. May serve some benefit in dark places, or at night.

name: Pauper's Rune
description: Grace that dwells within the inhabitants of The Lands Between; the lingering residue of gold. Use to gain a few runes. For all that they may be feeble things, these runes will act as nourishment for the development of any Tarnished. Provided a Finger Maiden can be found...

name: Flask Of Wondrous Physick
description: A relic of the physick chemists, priests of the Erdtree. Harnesses the powers of crystal tears, which only form after the passage of many moons. Various specials effects are bestowed upon the drinker, dependent on the specific mixture of crystal tears. Rest at a site of grace to replenish. It is said that in the Lands Between, pools of crystal tears amass at the bases of Minor Erdtrees.

name: Immunizing Cured Meat

name: Fireproof Dried Liver

name: Drawstring Fire Grease
description: Solidified grease made from a mixture of incendiary materials. Craftable item. A smallish lump with a short string attached. Quickly coats armament, inflicting fire damage. However, the effects are only brief.

name: Exalted Flesh
description: A lump of animal pickled in a medicinal solution mixed with fiery spices. Craftable item. Temporarily Boosts physical attack Considered a delicacy in the badlands, this invigorating repast was for the exclusive benefit of those who they called heroes.

name: Sleep Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a cracked pot. Filled with the incantations of St. Trina. Consumes FP. Throw at enemy to release a purple, soporific haze. Like a lullaby, or a quagmire, it irresistibly draws its victims down into sleep. Sweet dreams.

name: Gold-pickled Fowl Foot
description: Four-toed foot of a fowl, pickled in a golden medicinal solution. Craftable item. Boosts the amount of runes obtained from defeating enemies for a certain duration Since old times, the needy would scrape the meat clean even from a fowl's claw.

name: Dragon Heart
description: Dragon heart seized by a dragon tracker. It has a bizarre shape, mottled by gravel, and it continues to beat vivaciously. An offering used in the Dragon Communion. Consume a dragon's heart at the altar to make its power yours. While a terrible and savage-looking thing, the heart has a peculiar beauty to it.

name: Furlcalling Finger Remedy
description: Item for online play. Craftable item. Reveals cooperative and competitive multiplayer signs. Co-op summoning signs will be shown in gold, while hostile summoning signs will be shown in red. Multiplayer begins when you summon a player from another world through their sign.

name: Roped Fetid Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a cracked pot. A cocktail of effluents is sealed inside, and a short rope that aids throwing has been secured around the pot. Throw at rearward enemies to cause buildup of deadly poison. Beware though; those who carry these pots will slowly accumulate poison in their own bodies. Push someone in a privy; expect to get dung on your hands.

name: Roped Poison Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a cracked pot. A cocktail of poisonous materials is sealed inside, and a short rope that aids throwing has been secured around the pot. Throw at rearward enemies to cause buildup of poison.

name: Beastlure Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a ritual pot. Enchanted with assassin incantations. Consumes FP. Throw to create a red shadow. The illusion lures in beasts into attacking it. This effect does not change even during combat.

name: Roped Oil Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a cracked pot. A cocktail of oil-infused materials is sealed inside, and a short rope that aids throwing has been secured around the pot. Throw at rearward enemies to soak them in oil, making them heavily susceptible to fire damage.

name: Rancor Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a cracked pot. Enchanted by the ancient death hex. Consumes FP. Throw at enemies to spawn vengeful spirits that chase down foes. In times of old, the dead were burned with ghostflame, and from those cinders arose vengeful spirits.

name: Cursed-blood Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a ritual pot. Decorated with the crest of the Lord of Blood. Throw at enemies to douse them in accursed blood, causing summoned spirits to assail them with a rabid fervor. A childhood memory of the Lord of Blood.

name: Freezing Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a ritual pot. Engraved with the crest of the Carian Royals. Throw at enemies to cause buildup of frost. Originates from the cold, dark moon of Ranni, the Carian princess.

name: Poison Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a cracked pot. A cocktail of poisonous materials is sealed inside. Throw at enemies to cause buildup of poison.

name: Oil Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a cracked pot. A cocktail of oil-infused materials is sealed inside. Throw at enemies to soak them in oil, making them heavily susceptible to fire damage.

name: Poison Spraymist
description: Forbidden art of depraved perfumers. Craftable with a perfume bottle. Uses FP to release a poison mist from user's mouth, causing a buildup of poison. Perfumed powder is held in the mouth to dissolve before being expelled. It was once a restorative art, or so it is said.

name: Fetid Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a cracked pot. A cocktail of effluents is sealed inside. As the mixture ferments, toxins are produced alongside a putrid stench that seeps out once ripe. Throw at enemies to cause buildup of deadly poison. Beware though; those who carry these pots will slowly accumulate poison in their own bodies. Push someone in a privy; expect to get dung on your hands.

name: Giantsflame Fire Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a ritual pot. Enchanted by incantations of the Giants' Flame. Consumes FP. Throw at enemies to inflict heavy fire damage. Damage scales with faith.

name: Bloodboil Aromatic
description: Forbidden art of depraved perfumers. Craftable with a perfume bottle. Uses FP to enter a temporary state of fervor, raising maximum attack power and stamina while also increasing damage received. "Even upon the battlefield, do you fear being wounded? Take a good look. Your limbs are frozen stiff."

name: Thawfrost Boluses
description: Ice-hued boluses made from cave moss. Craftable item.

name: Remembrance Of The Naturalborn
description: Remembrance of Astel, Naturalborn of the Void, hewn into the Erdtree.  The power of its namesake can be unlocked by the Finger Reader. Alternatively, it can be used to gain a great bounty of runes.

name: Remembrance Of The Regal Ancestor
description: Remembrance of the Regal Ancestor Spirit, hewn into the Erdtree.

name: Margit's Shackle
description: A fetish bathed in golden magic. Shackles were used to bind the accursed people called the Omen, and these ones were made to keep a particular Omen under strictest confinement. Though faint, the shackles still retain vestiges of power — enough to trap the once-bound Margit on earth, if only for a short time.

Highly effective against Those Who Live in Death, even preventing them from rising again. The Golden Order has no mercy for those who trespass beyond life's bounds.

name: Rot Pot
description: Craftable item prepared using a ritual pot. Decorated with the crest of scarlet wings. Throw at enemies to cause buildup of scarlet rot.  The rot bubbles up from the Swamp of Aeonia, and eats away at life like a vicious plague.

name: Spark Aromatic
description: Art of the perfumers who fought In the Shattering. Craftable with a perfume bottle. Uses FP to broadly scatter sparks in a wide arc straight ahead. Though fire was prohibited to those who served the Erdtree, this rule was forgotten as the war drew ever on.

Alternatively, it can be used to gain a great bounty of runes. Maliketh was a shadowbound beast given to his Empyrean. Marika's sole need of her shadow was a vessel to lock away Destined Death. Even then, she betrayed him.

description: Memento left by the chrysalids sacrificed for grafting. A brooch wrapped in red velvet. Traces of blood are visible.

name: Chrysalids' Memento
description: Memento left by the chrysalids sacrificed for grafting. A brooch wrapped in red velvet. Traces of blood are visible.

name: Beast Eye
description: Claw-marked stone eye received from Gurranq, Beast Clergyman.

name: Deathroot
description: A source that gives rise to Those Who Live in Death.

name: Shabriri Grape
description: A yellowing, oozing eyeball of the infirm. The surface is shriveled, and the inside is squishy, not unlike a large, overly-ripe grape.

name: Celestial Dew
description: A hidden Tear found in the Eternal City. Also known as a Night Tear.

name: Seedbed Curse
description: Curse grown on a corpse killed and defiled by the Dung Eater. A tender pox afflicted with omen horns.

name: Black Knifeprint
description: On the Night of the Black Knives, someone stole a fragment of Death from Maliketh, the Black Blade, and imbued its power into the assassins' daggers.

name: Dragon Heart
description: Dragon heart seized by a dragon tracker. It has a bizarre shape, mottled by gravel, and it continues to beat vivaciously. An offering used in the Dragon Communion. Consume a dragon's heart at the altar to make its power yours. While a terrible and savage-looking thing, the heart has a peculiar beauty to it.

name: Fingerprint Grape
description: Eyeball of the knight Vyke, inflamed yellow.

name: Prattling Pate "hello"
description: Twisted clay sculpt in the shape of a human head.

name: Prattling Pate "thank You"
description: Twisted clay sculpt in the shape of a human head.

name: Prattling Pate "apologies"
description: Twisted clay sculpt in the shape of a human head. Emits a voice that says "Apologies."

name: Wraith Calling Bell
description: Bell used by worshippers of revenants.

name: Larval Tear
description: Core of a creature of mimicry known as a silver tear.

name: Seluvis's Potion
description: Small flask received from Preceptor Seluvis containing a cloudy tonic of bluish black.

name: Mirage Riddle
description: A riddle concerning a rise that vanishes like a mirage.

name: Valkyrie's Prosthesis
description: Golden prosthesis once used by the one-armed valkyrie. A masterwork of craftsmanship, with practice and skill it can be used as proficiently as a real arm. When Maleigh Marais, Lord of the Shaded Castle, embraced this prosthesis, he claimed to feel the presence of his personal goddess.

name: Weathered Dagger
description: Dagger received from Fia, the Deathbed Companion.

name: Seluvis's Introduction
description: Scroll bearing a royal coat of arms.

name: Lost Ashes Of War
description: Empty ashes of war, devoid of any memories of battle.

name: Fingerslayer Blade
description: The hidden treasure of the Eternal City of Nokron; a blade said to have been born of a corpse.

name: Ancestral Infant's Head
description: Skull of a very young ancestral spirit. Just think how many sproutings It might bear.

name: Carian Inverted Statue
description: Statuette of a scholar, with ground and sky inverted.

name: Cursemark Of Death
description: Cursemark carved into the discarded flesh of Ranni the Witch. Also known as the half-wheel wound of the centipede.

name: Rold Medallion
description: Conjoined split medallion depicting the Flame Peak. Brandishing the medallion activates the Grand Lift of Rold, connecting Leyndell to the Mountaintops of the Giants. The forge of the flame of ruin is said to be found upon their peaks, and it is here Melina wishes to travel in resuming your journey together.

name: Miniature Ranni
description: A doll resembling Ranni the Witch.

name: The Stormhawk King
description: Ashes of a hawk revered by all others as sovereign back in the days when Stormveil's winds still raged like no other. This ancient monarch is proud however, refusing to answer anyone's summons.

name: Dark Moon Ring
description: Ring depicting a leaden full moon. Symbolic of a cold oath, the ring is supposed to be given by Lunar Princess Ranni to her consort.

name: Dectus Medallion (right)
description: Right half of a split medallion depicting the Erdtree.

name: Haligtree Secret Medallion (left)
description: Left half of a split medallion depicting the Haligtree. Brandishing the medallion with both halves conjoined will activate the Grand Lift of Rold, granting access to a hidden path. In other words, this secret medallion will guide the bearer to the land of Miquella's Haligtree.

name: Haligtree Secret Medallion (right)
description: Right half of a split medallion depicting the Haligtree. Brandishing the medallion with both halves conjoined will activate the Grand Lift of Rold, granting access to a hidden path. In other words, this secret medallion will guide the bearer to the land of Miquella's Haligtree.

name: Assassin's Prayerbook
description: Prayerbook of the Roundtable Hold's assassins.

name: Dectus Medallion (left)
description: Left half of a split medallion depicting the Erdtree.

name: Fire Monks' Prayerbook
description: Prayerbook of the Fire Monks, who came from the Mountaintops of the Giants far to the north.

name: Dragon Cult Prayerbook
description: Prayerbook of the capital's ancient dragon cult.

name: Two Fingers Prayerbook
description: Prayerbook containing incantations of the Two Fingers. An item once entrusted to Tarnished worthy of lordship.

name: Ancient Dragon Prayerbook
description: Prayerbook of the capital's ancient dragon cult. A lost tome that never reached the Lands Between.

name: Royal House Scroll
description: Sorcery scroll of the Carian royal family, the heads of the Academy of Raya Lucaria.

name: Academy Scroll
description: Scroll of the Academy of Raya Lucaria, the glintstone sorcerers' place of study.

name: Whetstone Knife
description: Whetstone with a cipher inscription, made to look like a small knifeblade.

name: Glintstone Whetblade
description: Glintstone whetblade with a cipher engraved. Can be used as a whetstone knife.

name: Iron Whetblade
description: Iron whetblade with a cipher engraved. Can be used as a whetstone knife.

name: Whetstone Knife
description: Whetstone with a cipher inscription, made to look like a small knifeblade.

name: Black Whetblade
description: Black whetblade with a cipher engraved. Can be used as a whetstone knife.

name: Sancrified Whetblade
description: Sanctified whetblade with a cipher engraved. Can be used as a whetstone knife. When applying an affinity using physical or golden-type ashes of war, an additional affinity of sacred or lightning can be chosen.

name: Map (limgrave, West)
description: Map of the western region of Limgrave. The demesne of Limgrave, far south of the Erdtree, is bordered to the northwest by the cliffs of Stormveil, and under its ever-clouded skies roll the great steppes of the pale lands.

name: Map (limgrave, East)
description: Map of the eastern region of Limgrave.

name: Map (weeping Peninsula)
description: Map of the Weeping Peninsula.

name: Map (weeping Peninsula)
description: Map of the Weeping Peninsula.

name: Map (liurnia, East)
description: Map of Liurnia's eastern region.

name: Map (liurnia, North)
description: Map of Liurnia's northern region.

name: Map (dragonbarrow)
description: Map of Dragonbarrow and environs.

name: Map (liurnia, West)
description: Map of Liurnia's western region.

name: Map (ainsel River)
description: Map of Ainsel River and environs

name: Map (siofra River)
description: Map of Siofra River and environs

name: Map (altus Plateau)
description: Map of Altus Plateau and environs. The Altus Plateau, where the Erdtree's base can be found, contains the Royal Capital of Leyndell to the east, and Mt. Gelmir to the west. Scars from the Shattering remain apparent to this day.

name: Map (leyndell, Royal Capital)
description: Map of the Royal Capital of Leyndell and environs.

name: Map (caelid)
description: Map of Caelid and environs.

name: Map (mountaintops Of The Giants, West)
description: Map of Western Mountaintops of the Giants. Marching ground during the War against the Giants. They carved winding paths in the cliff walls right up to the summit, leading to the untrodden snow-laden region beyond.

name: Map (mountaintops Of The Giants, East)
description: Map of Eastern Mountaintops of the Giants. The remote, desolate eastern summit is the highest point in all the Lands Between, overlooking even the Flame Peak to the south.

name: Map (consecrated Snowfield)
description: Map of Consecrated Snowfield and environs. The route through this land, crossed east to west by a frozen river, leads to Miquella's Haligtree. This is the path taken by those unchosen, though it is a trial all the same.

name: Map (lake Of Rot)
description: Map of Lake of Rot and environs. A great lake of standing water downstream of the Ainsel River. It is said that the divine essence of an outer god is sealed away in this land.

name: Note (land Squirts)
description: A note sold by a nomadic merchant. Contains information about land squirts.

name: Map (deeproot Depths)
description: Map of Deeproot Depths and environs. At the very depths of the Erdtree's majestic roots lies the source of the Ainsel and the Siofra rivers. Here too begins the network of Greattree roots that spread throughout the Lands Between.

name: Note (stonedigger Trolls)
description: A note sold by a nomadic merchant. Contains information about stonedigger trolls.

name: Note (flask Of Wondrous Physick)
description: A note sold by a nomadic merchant.

name: Note (waypoint Ruins)
description: A note sold by a nomadic merchant.

name: Ruptured Crystal Tear
description: A special crystallization formed within a tear of life over the course of many moons. Causes concoction to explode when taken in mixed physick. A dangerous form of crystal tear which possesses absolutely no medicinal qualities. A lesson said to be learned the hard way for some; faith can be a volatile matter, after all.

name: Note: Demi-human Mobs
description: Note imparting knowledge in brief.

name: Greenspill Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Cerulean Crystal Tear
description: A special crystallization formed over the course of many moons within a tear of life, a blessing of the Erdtree. Can be mixed in a flask of wondrous physick. The resulting concoction restores 20 half of one's max FP.

name: Cerulean Hidden Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Crimson Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction restores half of one's maximum HP.

name: Crimsonburst Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's

name: Faith-knot Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction temporarily boosts one's faith.

name: Strength-knot Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Opaline Bubbletear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Spiked Cracked Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Dexterity-knot Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Lightning-shrouding Cracked Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Magic-shrouding Cracked Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Winged Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Holy-shrouding Cracked Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Twiggy Cracked Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Leaden Hardtear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Crimsonspill Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction temporarily raises one's maximum HP.

name: Greenburst Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction gradually restores stamina recovery speed.

name: Speckled Hardtear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction temporarily raises all resistances and heals all status ailments.

name: Flame-shrouding Cracked Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction temporarily boosts the power of one's fire attacks.

name: Crimson Bubbletear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction automatically heals one's HP in the moment before death. However, this effect only occurs once, and will expire after a certain duration.

name: Crimsonwhorl Bubbletear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction converts incoming damage into recovered HP instead. However, physical damage cannot be converted. This effect is only brief and will quickly expire.

name: Thorny Cracked Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction makes consecutive attacks grow stronger the longer they continue. However, the effect lasts only for a short time.

name: Stonebarb Cracked Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Windy Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction increases the effectiveness of dodgerolls for a certain duration. However, damage taken is also increased during the concoction's effect.

name: Opaline Hardtear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wondrous Physick. The resulting concoction temporarily boosts all forms of damage negation.

name: Purifying Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the age where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground. Can be mixed in the Flask of Wonderous Physick. The resulting conction purifies the curse from Mohg, Lord of Blood's terrifying rite of blood.

name: Aeonian Butterfly
description: A butterfly with withered, scarlet wings found in the swamp of Aeonia. Material used for crafting items.

name: Albinauric Bloodclot
description: The thick, coagulated blood of the Ablinaurics. Material used for crafting items.

name: Intelligence-knot Crystal Tear
description: A crystal tear formed slowly over the ages where the Erdtree's bounty falls to the ground.

name: Altus Bloom
description: A golden-tingerd flower from a succulent plant that blooms on the Altus Plateau. Material used for crafting items.

name: Arteria Leaf
description: Dark red leaves with thick, swollen veins. Material used for crafting items. Exceedingly rare to find. A faint pulse can be felt in the veins. Stirs the blood, providing an enlivening effect.

name: Beast Liver
description: The fresh liver of a beast; a luscious fruit of life. Material used for crating items. Found by hunting herbivorous beast. Dried liver boost damage negation.

name: Beast Blood
description: Fresh beast blood, glinting with gold. Material used for crafting items.

name: Bloodrose
description: Blood-slick roses that bloom in festering blood. Material used for crafting items.

name: Blood-tainted Excrement
description: The bloody excrement of a carnivorous beast. Material used for crafting items. Found in the land of the new dynasty. Mixed inside with half-digested flesh are dense colonies of tiny eggs of unknown but assuredly revolting origin.

name: Budding Cave Moss
description: Faintly luminescent moss that grows in dark caves, speckled with tiny, yellow flowers. Material used for crafting items.

name: Cave Moss
description: Faintly luminescent moss that grows in dark caves. Material used in crafting items. A fundamental ingredient for medicinal boluses.
extra_json: {"image": "https://eldenring.fanapis.com/images/items/17f69956f50l0i20oaky1f6im9a4n.png", "obtainedFrom": "Gives off pale light in dark caverns.", "type": "Misc"}

name: Cracked Crystal
description: A cracked, impure, degraded, and altogether unremarkable crystal. Material used for crafting items

name: Crystal Cave Moss
description: Faintly luminescent moss that grows in dark caves, laced with fine crystals. Material used for crafting items.

name: Budding Horn
description: A rarely-seen specimen of a young, budding horn. Material used for crafting items. Found by hunting herbivorous beasts.

name: Crab Eggs
description: Eggs of lare crabs which dwell in the shallows. Materials used for crafting items.

name: Cracked Pot
description: This empty pot somehow mends itself when broken.

name: Ritual Pot
description: This empty pot somehow mends itself when broken. Special item with greater durability than a cracked pot.

name: Crystal Bud
description: A young plant, crystalized before it could mature. Material used for crafting items.

name: Dewkissed Herba
description: A herb that grows in the false night in and around the Eternal City. Material used for crafting items.

name: Eye Of Yelough
description: A shrub fruit bursting with ripened pulp. Material used for crafting items.

name: Erdleaf Flower
description: A dusky-yellow flower that has started to fade and wilt. Material used for crafting items.

name: Faded Erdleaf Flower
description: An Erdleaf flower that has faded into a plate scarlet, found blooming in rotten lands. Material used for crafting items.

name: Fire Blossom
description: A half-ashen and smoldering flower that blooms on the mountaintops of the Giants. Material used for crafting items.

name: Flight Pinion
description: Flight feather of a bird of prey. Material used for crafting items. Commonly used for arrow fletchings.

name: Formic Rock
description: Rock formed from solidified giant ant venom. Highly acidic. Material used for crafting items.

name: Four-toed Fowl Foot
description: Foot of a four-toed fowl. Material used for crafting items. In the Lands Between, having three digits is seen as a bad omen. As such, the rarer four-toed fowl's is a gift of great luck indeed.

name: Fulgurbloom
description: Yellow flower that grows in lightning-struck lands. Material used for crafting items. Imbued with traces of lightning's essence.

name: Glintstone Firefly
description: A firefly whose glowing tail has hardened into glintstone, widely found in Liurnia Lake. Material used for crafting items.

name: Glintstone Scrap
description: Piece of glintstone tinged with unstable magic. Found in crystal tunnels. Break gem, using FP to produce a magic bolt. Poor quality and thereby easily broken, a sorcerer wouldn't give it a second look.

name: Gold Firefly
description: Firefly that gives off a golden light. Material used in crafting items. Found near bodies of water close to Minor Erdtrees. The light of fireflies is believed to have an alluring magic. Golden light is considered to invite runes.

name: Gold-tinged Excrement
description: Someone's excrement. It has a golden tinge. Material used for crafting items. Often hidden in woods and thickets. Gold-tinged excrement is a highly stable substance; it doesn't dry out, nor does it lose its customary warmth or scent. For better or for worse, it remains as it is.

name: Golden Centipede
description: The golden, desiccated remains of a centipede.

name: Golden Dung
description: Someone's excrement. It has a golden tinge. Material used for crafting items. Gold-tinged excrement is a highly stable substance; it doesn't dry out, nor does it lose its customary warmth or scent. For better or for worse, it remains as it is.

name: Golden Rowa
description: A Rowa fruit tinted with gold. Material used for crafting items.

name: Golden Sunflower
description: A golden sunflower that grows facing the Erdtree. Material used for crafting items. Found near Minor Erdtrees.

name: Grave Violet
description: A purple flower than blooms in graveyards. Material used for crafting items.

name: Gravel Stone
description: A small clump of sharp, pointed stones. Material used for crafting items.

name: Great Dragonfly Head
description: Head of a large dragonfly. Material used for crafting items. Long believed to have the ability to neutralize poisons.

name: Herba
description: Evergreen leaves that give off a faith light. Material used for crafting items. This very common medicinal plant can be found in thickets and elsewhere.

name: Hidden Plumage
description: Rarely-seen dark plumage found inside the wing. Material used for crafting items. Death's bearers were once said to have taken the form of birds, symbolized by these black feathers.

name: Human Bone Shard
description: Fragment of bone with dun mottling. Material used for crafting items. Found by hunting Those Who Live in Death.

name: Living Jar Shard
